  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken breast portions </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650366987150-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650366987150-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650366987150-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650366987150-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650366987150-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a couple of splashes of <strong>water</strong> to the pan and cover with a lid</p><p>Cook for a further 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once cooked through, transfer the chicken to a plate and reserve the pan</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650367085139-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650367085139-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650367085139-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650367085139-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650367085139-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a large baking tray with the <strong>paprika</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the fries are golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1650367102738-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1650367102738-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1650367102738-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1650367102738-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1650367102738-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Melt 20g <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g] </span><strong>butter </strong>in a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 20g <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span><strong> flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms — this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk the <strong>chicken stock</strong> in a little at a time, and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Stir the <strong>Henderson's Relish </strong>through the sauce — this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1650367118416-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1650367118416-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1650367118416-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1650367118416-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1650367118416-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash, then rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Heat the reserved pan with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a bite</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – these are your <strong>buttered greens</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1650367146388-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1650367146388-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1650367146388-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1650367146388-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1650367146388-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain the <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Chop the <strong>mozzarella</strong> into small pieces</p><p>Once the sweet potato fries are cooked, push them apart to form 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> piles on the tray</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped mozzarella </strong>to each pile and return to the oven for 4-5 min or until the cheese has melted – these are your <strong>cheesy sweet potato fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1650367167364-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1650367167364-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1650367167364-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1650367167364-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1650367167364-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Shred the <strong>chicken</strong> apart using two forks – this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p><p>Add the <strong>pulled chicken</strong> to the<strong> gravy</strong>, increase the heat to medium-high and cook for 1-2 min or until everything’s hot</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1650367222049-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1650367222049-x400.jpg",
